 on Fasting: When sun sets, time for Iftar","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 15, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the night approaches from the east and day retreats from the west and the sun has set, it is time to break the fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1954, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1100 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23295,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/06\/23\/siyam-sawm-lies-obscenity-sins\/","url_meta":{"origin":24891,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Siyam: True fasting is from falsehood and sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 23, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, fasting is not only from eating and drinking. Rather, fasting is from vanity and obscenity. If someone abuses you or acts foolish against you, then say: Indeed, I am fasting.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 3479\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3795,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/24\/accidentally-break-fast-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":24891,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: One who accidentally breaks fast completes it","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever eats or drinks forgetfully while he is fasting, let him complete his fast, for Allah has fed him and given him drink.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1933, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1155 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15071,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/15\/sunset-break-fast-maghrib\/","url_meta":{"origin":24891,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Time to break fast at sunset, Maghrib","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 15, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Abi Awfa reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen you see the sun set and night has come from the east, it is time to break the fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1956, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1101 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/24891","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}]